(2191, 6, '2015-05-28 21:18:37', '2015-05-28 21:18:37', '<a href="http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2015/05/beauty1.jpg"><img class="  aligncenter wp-image-2192" title="influencer marketing " src="http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2015/05/beauty1.jpg" alt="influencer marketing " width="601" height="498" /></a>\r\n\r\nIn the history of <em>influencer marketing campaigns</em> - one of the hottest industries, some of the biggest and earliest successes - came from the makeup and fashion worlds. As user generated content began to gain traction online, makeup, fashion, and style-related blogs and video commentators appeared in huge numbers. Because of the broad interest in this topic, these influencers quickly gained wide followings. Brands learned that a recommendation or a how-to post from a respected beauty blogger or vlogger could move products and generate buzz faster than a traditional advertisement. Here are several takeaways that brands can learn from the beauty, fashion, and makeup industry influencer campaigns:<!--more-->\r\n<h2>Focus on long-tail influencers</h2>\r\nIn many ways, the early influencer marketing pioneers working with makeup reviewers on YouTube and fashion bloggers defined what our modern definition of an <em>influencer </em>is. It’s easy to fall prey to the illusion that an effective influencer is someone with a big following. It certainly helps. Still, it is critical to look at their subject matter expertise and their actual relationship with followers. Someone who has a smaller following that is loyal and takes action based on their content is much more valuable than someone with larger numbers whose content is largely ignored.\r\n\r\nThe fashion world provided great insights into the power of a long-tail influencer. Style is a highly subjective topic. An expert that is teaching teens the fundamentals of applying makeup is very different than say, a thirty-something professional interested in plus-size clothes for professional attire. The power of an influencer to really grow a product\'s following requires honing in on who they really are, what they are saying, and what demographics really comprise their followers. Long-tail influencers with super specialized interests like Asian-derived cosmetics, the Paleo diet, or thrift-store vintage finds are the backbone of influencer campaigns in the beauty world.\r\n<h2>Cross-platform influence matters</h2>\r\nBrands that are building influencer campaigns have begun to move beyond Facebook and Twitter. Social video is a major focus. It’s easy to understand why. According to the <a href="http://www.reelseo.com/youtube-google-search-results/">latest studies</a>, video appears in 55% of Google keyword searches and 85% of those are from YouTube. Other video networks – including Vine, Instagram, and more – will comprise an increasingly important percentage of those results over time. We know that the more traction that brands get with influencer content on different networks, the more reach they’ll have over time with active social media audiences and even in terms of organic search.\r\n\r\nThe sophistication of influencer brands is increasingly taking content creators cross-platform. Someone who launched on Instagram and grew a healthy following on a specific topic is often watching to see which new social networks are taking hold. After all, they will want to keep their own brands relevant and always in front of fans. Beauty brands have long invested in social marketing campaigns that can gain them exposure on multiple networks. This strategy translates into a big benefit for brands seeking influencer campaigns, as they gain wide cross-platform exposure by sharing content from Vine on Instagram, Twitter, and the seemingly endless new platforms.\r\n<h2>Authenticity matters in influencer marketing selection</h2>\r\nAuthenticity matters: the authenticity of the influencer’s passion for your product or service and the authentic voice of the message that they share with their followers. How do brands measure authenticity? It’s essential that you have access to both experienced individuals in the influencer marketing space to guide campaign creation and detailed analytics. As influencer marketing is becoming a hot topic, consumers are growing wary of big name social media stars that will promote any brand for money.\r\n\r\nDelving into the profile and past content of an influencer is key, as well as understanding their relationship with their audience. An influencer with a highly engaged following is one that’s trusted and respected. Often, this is another reason that long-tail influencers are a better fit for campaigns. Their content is likely to feature fewer endorsements, so their audiences are much more receptive. Partnering with an agency like FullBottle will ensure that you’re able to determine and weigh all of these factors before selecting a potential influencer to work with.\r\n<h2>Guided letting go leads to better content</h2>\r\nAnother lesson in influencer campaigns from the beauty industry is that letting go often leads to better content. Ideating on creative approaches to marketing your brands and products on an ongoing basis is a challenge. Yet the best brand management instincts of a company often suggest that it’s important to hold tight to brand identity and control. Some creative control is essential, with brand guidelines and campaign communications goals. But ultimately, you have to trust the influencers you’re selecting to communicate effectively with their audiences.\r\n\r\nAs <a href="http://www.forbes.com/sites/kylewong/2014/12/22/how-influencer-marketing-will-change-in-2015/2/">one expert stated in an insightful piece</a> on <em>Forbes</em>, “brands should trust digital influencers who have an intimate understanding of how their millions of fans will respond so the brand message is delivered both organically and effectively. Brands must alter their thinking when it comes to influencers and their fans. Instead of saying “do this,” they should be asking “what should we do?” Taking advantage of your influencers\' creativity can take your brand expression to a whole new level that effectively resonates with the audiences you’re seeking to reach.\r\n\r\nAre you interested in putting these lessons to work for your company’s next influencer marketing campaign? <a href="http://localhost:8888/brands/">Contact FullBottle</a> today to learn more about our solutions and services.', '4 Lessons from the Fashion Industry\'s Pioneering Use of Influencer Marketing', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', '4-lessons-from-the-fashion-industrys-pioneering-use-of-influencer-marketing', '', '', '2015-05-28 21:18:37', '2015-05-28 21:18:37', '', 0, 'http://localhost:8888/?p=2191', 0, 'post', '', 0),
