(2306, 6, '2015-06-02 16:26:33', '2015-06-02 16:26:33', '<a href="http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/instagram.png"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-2293 size-full" title="instagram" src="http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/instagram.png" alt="instagram" width="288" height="378" /></a>\r\n\r\nOne <a href="http://simplymeasured.com/blog/2015/04/23/50-of-instagram-comments-come-within-10-hours-of-posting/">recent study</a> suggests that 50% of comments on Instagram come in the first 10 hours. 69% of all comments happen within the first 48 hours. What this means is that unlike other networks which may be more evergreen in their structure (like Pinterest for example), speed is of the essence when building momentum for your branded Instagram campaigns.  Does your influencer marketing campaign have the right elements in place to capitalize on Instagram\'s speed of engagement? Let’s take a closer look at what brands can to do to get the highest ROI on their campaigns and engage fans and followers during those critical first hours.<!--more-->\r\n<h2>What Does Engagement Look Like on Instagram?</h2>\r\nIt’s important to define engagement on Instagram. The site has more than 300 million active monthly users, 70 million photos posted per day, and over 2.5 billion likes per day. It’s easy to see with this volume of information why early engagement becomes critical. Simply Measured’s study further revealed that brand usage is growing and that engagement with brand posts is growing faster than brands are adopting the network. This gap represents an opportunity for brands that are willing to take the plunge to both stand out and develop meaningful connections with the audience.\r\n\r\nIn the study, each Instagram post by an Interbrand 100 brand averaged 20,795 likes or comments and average engagement per post has grown by 83%. With all this brand engagement happening, it’s easy to see why companies are focusing on Instagram. But what steps should brands be taking to capture that early engagement?\r\n<h2>Make Meaningful Connections</h2>\r\nEngaging with other users is essential to growing your followers and promoting likes and comments on your posts. Ultimately, the stronger your follower base the more interaction that you’ll see around each post. Cultivating relationships of mutual engagement is important; how often you like or comment on other content has a reciprocal factor. However, there are also several structural things that can be done when posts are released to help boost their visibility. For example, posts that include a @userhandle mention get 38% more engagement than those that don’t. Does your post reference someone’s work or is it of particular interest to them? Be sure to strategically tag them. These simple forms of outreach can play a major role in catching people’s attention and ensuring that the likes and comments begin to roll in.\r\n\r\nFocus on Findability\r\nAnother essential component to gaining traction with Instagram posts is focusing on findability. Within Instagram, hashtags are a great way to get your videos and images into the larger conversation. As with any network, the key trending hashtags are always changing; others are part of an ongoing conversation and are evergreen. Here is a list of constantly updated <a href="http://top-hashtags.com/instagram/">popular hashtags</a>. Promoting your posts through the Promoted Posts program is another way to get increased visibility as soon as materials are published.\r\n<h2>Follow the Filter Trends + Other Trends</h2>\r\nInstagram is an artistic network. When you’re considering static images, you can increase engagement simply by <a href="http://populagram.appspot.com/filters">using a popular filter</a>. Images that follow the key trends tend to visually stand out in a user’s image feed and often garner higher levels of engagement. Be aware of what trends are leading the way on images and videos. Employ those for an aesthetic that appeals to your audience. Or, in certain cases, take a very unique approach to differentiate yourself from the flow of imagery that users are looking at. Be deliberate when choosing your visual presentation and artistic direction.\r\n<h2>Engage Social Influencers</h2>\r\nAnother way to quickly amplify the reach of your Instagram campaigns is by taking part in an influencer marketing campaign. By working with Influencers, you are tapping into their existing networks of engaged followers and immediately getting eyes on content related to your brand. When partnering with an experienced influencer marketing agency like fullbottle, you’re connecting with an infrastructure that’s build to support the world of fast engagement on Instagram. From the influencers that are chosen to how content is created, each step is executed for maximum ROI. Investing in a social media video campaign is one of the best ways to ensure that your content is widely seen, disseminated, and engaged with.\r\n\r\nGetting the most out of Instagram requires a deep understanding of how the network functions. Brands are seeing a tremendous return on their investments, but it’s important to understand how content should be created and disseminated to work with the unique engagement timelines of Instagram. Are you interested in learning more about social video influencer marketing campaigns? <a href="http://www.fullbottlegroup.com/brands/">Contact fullbottle today</a> to learn more about our solutions and services.', 'Understanding the Speed of Engagement on Instagram', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '2292-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-06-02 16:26:33', '2015-06-02 16:26:33', '', 2292, 'http://localhost:8888/2292-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(2307, 6, '2015-06-02 16:27:24', '2015-06-02 16:27:24', '<a href="http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/brendon.png"><img class="  aligncenter wp-image-2290" title="social video marketing Vine" src="http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/brendon.png" alt="social video marketing Vine" width="703" height="442" /></a>\r\n\r\nPanic! At the Disco, a popular band, recently took to the stage to play during the Shorty Awards. But they also hit the red carpet and one of the band’s members, Brendon Urie, gave the International Business Times <a href="http://www.ibtimes.com/how-be-successful-vine-advice-panic-disco-singer-brendon-urie-1892218">a great interview</a> on building a strong following on Vine. Urie has almost a million followers on the social video platform, and has some helpful recommendations for how brands can build a compelling presence there. The central insight was the importance of a developing authentic voice for your brand on Vine. Let’s take a closer look at Panic!’s example and explore how developing an authentic voice can help propel your brand’s social media marketing to the next level.\r\n<h2>Go Behind the Scenes</h2>\r\nA major point that Urie made was thinking about how to use Vine to tell your story. There are other platforms to post in-depth presentations, product photos, or explainer videos. What do your fans, followers, and customers want to see from you that can be conveyed in six seconds? For Panic! at the Disco, life on the road and behind the scenes previews have made for hot content. In the interview, Urie said: “When musicians are using it it’s like a shot of them on tour, which is always fun. It’s a little different than singing live. But it gives insight, which is cool.”\r\n\r\nThe idea of giving fans insight into your brand and products is spot on for how to think about content creation. The question is how to translate that general paradigm to your specific industry and your company’s personality. Many brands have had success with fun videos showing customers with their products; developing quick, funny loops; and cultivating user generated content (UCG) campaigns. Find something unique and meaningful to say that aligns with your brand, and keep the network’s lighter tone in mind.\r\n<h2>Find Your Authentic Voice</h2>\r\nFor Urie, authentic correlates with original: whether it’s original material or putting a fresh spin on a more staid topic, being different is key. “So I think the original thing works out a little better, as long as you’re not trying to copy someone straight up, because that just sucks. Do some original stuff. That’s my advice,” he says. The story was interesting: originally he set up an account on the site to mimic the routines of his favorite comics. His strategy quickly evolved into developing his own voice and approach to relating with fans. Today, fans follow him for both his personal comedic material and the insider views of band life.\r\n\r\nConsidering what types of content appeals to you – and by extension to your core demographic – is a great start. Is the tone playful, evocative, emotional or educational? An authentic voice reverberates through every aspect of your content creation, from how you position your account to the content that you share. It’s about what you’re saying, the tone you’re using, and the visuals that underscore that messaging. All of these elements comprise your brand’s voice and how those impact the viewer experience.\r\n<h2>3 Tips for Conveying Your Authentic Voice in Social Video</h2>\r\n<em>Focus on the what and the how:</em> When you’re developing your voice, it’s important to remember that this includes both what you say and how you want to say it. Adjusting both the content and tone of Vines to your audience and objective ensures that your content hits the mark. Think about how you want your audience to feel when they see your content. What do you want the call to action to be when they see it?\r\n\r\n<em>Find a unique angle:</em> You’re probably contributing a video on a topic or issue that’s widely discussed on social media and social video. Ask yourself, what is your unique position? Uncovering that – what you have to say that’s different from everyone else out there – gives you a great starting point for developing innovative and authentic content that’s all your own.\r\n\r\n<em>Leverage the power of influencers:</em> Counterintuitively, one of the best ways to find your brand’s unique voice on social video may be to surrender some creative control to others. By working with influencers who deeply understand Vine, it’s possible to leverage their knowledge to create effective content that supports your brand’s goals. The best way to achieve this is by partnering with an experienced influence marketing agency like fullbottle, who will help you identify influencers whose work, voices, and tones is complementary to what you’re trying to achieve.\r\n\r\nAre you interested in learning more about social video influencer marketing campaigns? <a href="http://www.fullbottlegroup.com/brands/">Contact fullbottle today</a> to learn more about our solutions and services.', 'Developing an Authentic Brand Voice for Social Video Marketing: Lessons on Vine from Panic! At the Disco     ', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '2288-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-06-02 16:27:24', '2015-06-02 16:27:24', '', 2288, 'http://localhost:8888/2288-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
